Git Architecture

WorkingArea:It is a place where we can edit a file and add the files in this workplace and are visible to all the branches unless added and commited

Index/Staging area: On git add, files are moved from workplace to Staging area, here we can save the changes.

Local repo: On git commit, files are moved from staging area to Local Repo.

central repo: On git Push, Push all the files from Local to central Repo.
